Title: Lots and Lots of Fire Honey
Description:
If Harmot wants to patch this sleeping boulder up and get him out of my pond, I'm all for it. 

Unfortunately, we used the last of my store of fire honey on Shalehoof's wound. I haven't had time to harvest any from the Cinderwold with all these elementals running amok. 

Head on down to the wold's edge and bring us some honey. You're going to need a lot.
ObjectivesText: Find a lot of Fire Honey.
CompletionText: Mind yourself in my forest. Cinderbees are dangerous, but we rely on them for the honey they produce for our mead.
RewardText:
You found this off of WHAT? A living honey e--

<Farnee stops her sentence before lowering her voice.>

Let's keep all mention of living fire honey between us. Harmot might get distracted and run off into danger if we tell him...
